Practical 2 – Working with Strings – basic String Operations

2.1 WAP to demonstrate Slicing Operations in Strings

text = "Hello, World!"
print("Original string:", text)
print("Sliced from index 0 to 5:", text[0:5])
print("Sliced from start to index 5:", text[1:5:2])
print("Sliced from index -6 to -1:", text[-6:-1])


2.2 WAP to demonstrate built in functions of Strings
string="my name is palak"
print("Original String:", string)
print("Capitalized:", string.capitalize())
print("Uppercase:", string.upper())
print("Lowercase:", string.lower())
print("Title Case:", string.title())
print(f"Count of '{n}':", string.count(n))
print(f"Index of '{is}':", string.find(is))
    

